ufw: ufw (a user friendly firewall)
ufw:
ufw: Developed to ease iptables firewall configuration, ufw provides a
ufw: user friendly way to create an IPv4 or IPv6 host-based firewall.
ufw: By default UFW is disabled.
ufw:
ufw: What does it mean?  It has come to mean 'Uncomplicated Firewall',
ufw: but you can change it to something more suitable if you want. If
ufw: you like it, you might pick 'Universal Firewall', or 'Ultimate
ufw: Firewall'. If you are not a fan, perhaps 'Unbearable Firewall'.
ufw: Have fun!
